p.value: Identification of item, date; RG-031: The Microwave Research Institute Technical Reports; box number; folder number; Poly Archives & Special Collections at Bern Dibner Library of Science and Technology.

The Microwave Research Institute was founded at the Polytechnic Institute of Brooklyn (now the Tandon School of Engineering) by Ernst Weber in 1945. It was later renamed the Weber Research Institute in his honor.
At this time, PIB-MRI reports from 1942-1963 are listed. Please check back frequently, as new reports are added.
